.TH RULER 3
.SH NAME
ruler \- ruler protocol and request format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <ruler.h>
.SH DESCRIPTION
The header
.B <ruler.h>
defines the ruler protocol used by clients and the
.MR ruler 4
daemon.
.PP
Clients write a request to the 9P file
.B query
(one attribute per line, newline-separated), then read the response (newline-separated
.IB key = value
lines).
All four request attributes are required.
.PP
Request attribute names:
.TP
.B RulerQuery
The subject to match against rules (e.g. absolute file path).
.TP
.B RulerClient
Client identifier (e.g.\ 
.BR acme ,
.BR sam ).
.TP
.B RulerEvent
Event name (e.g.\ 
.BR open ,
.BR save ).
.TP
.B RulerId
Identity of the caller (e.g. window id); not used for matching.
.PP
The 9P file used for request and response is
.BR RulerQueryFile ,
the string
.BR query .
.PP
The
.B Rulerreq
structure may be used to hold the four attributes before formatting; all fields must be set before use.
.SH SOURCE
.B \*9/include/ruler.h
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.MR ruler 4 ,
.MR ruler 7 ,
.MR 9pclient 3
